conn_section: "conn_t Back-Pointer  (timer_id field)" {
  style: {
    fill: "#fff7ed"
    stroke: "#ea580c"
    border-radius: 8
  }

  ct3: "conn_table[fd=3]\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nstate:    ACTIVE\nfd:       3\ntimer_id: 0   в†ђв”Ђв”Ђ" {
    style.fill: "#fed7aa"
    style.stroke: "#ea580c"
    style.border-radius: 4
  }
  ct5: "conn_table[fd=5]\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nstate:    ACTIVE\nfd:       5\ntimer_id: 2   в†ђв”Ђв”Ђ" {
    style.fill: "#fed7aa"
    style.stroke: "#ea580c"
    style.border-radius: 4
  }
  ct7: "conn_table[fd=7]\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nstate:    ACTIVE\nfd:       7\ntimer_id: 1   в†ђв”Ђв”Ђ" {
    style.fill: "#fed7aa"
    style.stroke: "#ea580c"
    style.border-radius: 4
  }

  back_note: |md
    **Back-pointer contract:**
    conn_table[fd].timer_id == heap_idx
    heap.entries[heap_idx].fd == fd

    **Maintained by every heap_swap():**
    entries[a].heap_idx = a
    entries[b].heap_idx = b
    conn_table[entries[a].fd].timer_id = a
    conn_table[entries[b].fd].timer_id = b

    **Enables O(log n) cancel:**
    timer_cancel(conn->timer_id)
    в†’ no linear scan needed
  | {
    style.fill: "#ffedd5"
    style.stroke: "#ea580c"
    style.border-radius: 6
  }
}

invariant: |md
  **Heap Invariant (must hold at all times):**
  в€Ђ i > 0 :  entries[ (iв€’1)/2 ].expiry_ms  в‰¤  entries[i].expiry_ms

  Equivalently: every parent expires **before or at the same time** as both its children.
  Consequence: entries[0] (the root) is **always the nearest-expiring timer**.

  compute_epoll_timeout() reads entries[0].expiry_ms in O(1) вЂ” no scan required.

  Violated by: inserting without sift_up В· removing without sift_down В· heap_swap without updating heap_idx and conn_t.timer_id
| {
  near: bottom-center
  style.fill: "#f0fdf4"
  style.stroke: "#16a34a"
  style.border-radius: 8
}

